        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:46PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 445 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
across northeastern Crockett and northwestern Schleicher Counties,
moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Us-190 Near The Crockett-Sutton County Line and The Intersection Of
Us 190 And Highway 163.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
